        <div class="intro border border-dark m-3 bg-light">
            <p class="h3 m-3 fw-bold">What is BMI?</p>
            <p class="m-3">Body Mass Index (BMI) is a calculation 
                that estimates body fat based on height and weight, used as a screening
                 tool to assess if someone is underweight, overweight, or obese.
                 It is a quick, inexpensive, and widely used measure to assess weight relative to height. While it's a valuable tool for population health studies, it's important to remember that BMI is not a direct measure of body fat and doesn't account for individual differences like muscle mass or bone density. Healthcare providers use BMI alongside other health assessments
                  to determine an individual's overall health status and risk factors. 
                </p>
        </div>
    </section>
    <section id="About">
